Mr. He Dongfeng, President of COMAC, visits Canadian aviation enterprises





Last Updated (Beijing Time):2013-03-21    Source:News Center of COMAC
 


 
Mr. He Dongfeng, President of Commercial Aircraft Corporation of China, Ltd. (COMAC), visited Pratt&Whitney and Bombardier Inc. on March 21th, 2013, and met with Mdm Maria Della Posta, Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing of Pratt&Whitney, and Guy C. Hachey, President and Chief Operation Officer of Bombardier Aerospace. 

Mr. He Dongfeng listened to the introduction of product development and global service network distribution of Pratt&Whitney and visited the engine production line of Pratt&Whitney in Montreal. 

In Bombardier Inc., Mr. He Dongfeng and his delegation visited the production line and laboratory of Bombardier C series. Mr. He Dongfeng hoped to strengthen in-depth exchange with Canadian aviation enterprises, further widen cooperation fields and jointly promote the development of the civil aircraft industry. Both sides developed in-depth exchange on aviation market prediction and product development.
 

 
Mr. He Dongfeng (R1) presented a gift to Mr. Guy C. Hachey (L1) on March 21th, 2013.
 

 
Mr. He Dongfeng (R7) and his delegation took a group photo with Mdm Maria Della Bosta (L5) on March 21th, 2013.
 
 







